----------------------Force vertical format-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
If our object gets printed in mixed format,lets horizontal+verical so to force vertical format for all documents:---
test>config.set("inspectCompact", false);
ðŸ“ŒOptional: Restore printing setiings to Default 
test>config.reset("inspectCompact");
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 ===============================================================
|MongoDB Spooling Using PowerShell Transcript                   |
================================================================
|How to use Start-Transcript & Stop-Transcript|
----------------------------------------------
STEP-1:---To start recording all MongoDB (mongosh) commands and outputs into a file, run:
PS> Start-Transcript "C:\Users\91829\OneDrive\1 MONGODB\1 SPOOL\mongo.log"
----------------------------------------------
STEP-2:--- write mongosh--to get into mongoshell
PS> mongosh
----------------------------------------------
step-3:-- write your all mongoDb commands
> use demo
> db.test.insertOne({name:"navin"})
> db.test.find()
----------------------------------------------
STEP-4:---After finishing MongoDB work inside mongosh, USE quit()-->to get out from mongosh
> quit()
----------------------------------------------
STEP-5:--- so now you will be in Poer Shell again, Use Stop-Transcript
PS> Stop-Transcript
>--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Full Example Workflow
--------------------------------------------------------------------
PS> Start-Transcript "C:\\Users\\91829\\OneDrive\\1 MONGODB\\1 SPOOL\\mongo.log"
PS> mongosh
> use demo
> db.test.insertOne({name:"Navin"})
> db.test.find()
> quit()
PS> Stop-Transcript
==============================================================================


